<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880930-0051 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: AmVestors Financial Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> AVFC </CO><IN> BBK </IN><TEXT>   AmVestors Financial Corp., Topeka, Kan., said it is making a special offer to holders of its 8 1/2% convertible debentures to entice them to convert their $18.2 million in debentures into common shares.    The life-insurance holding company said the debentures are convertible into 4.464 common shares for each $25 face amount, or a conversion price of $5.60.    If holders convert their shares before Oct. 17, the company said they will receive accrued interest through Oct. 31 as well as the regular five-cent dividend on their new common shares. The accrued interest is equal to about $21.42 per $1,000 face amount of bonds, and the dividends total about $8.90 per $1,000 face amount. If holders convert the debentures between Oct. 17 and Nov. 1, they will receive accrued interest through Oct. 31. In over-the-counter trading yesterday, AmVestors closed at $7.125, down 12.5 cents. </TEXT></DOC>